xs = range(len(df))
series_x = []
for i in range(1991, 2018):
    if i in df.values:
        series_x.append(i)
    else:
        series_x.append(None)
series1 = np.array(series_x).astype(np.double)
s1mask = np.isfinite(series1)

#start, end = ax.get_ylim()
#ax.yaxis.set_ticks(np.arange(start, end, 100000))

#ax.set_ylim(0, 100000000)

ax.plot(series1[s1mask], df['population'], linestyle='-', marker='o', label="National population")
ax.plot(series1[s1mask], df['graduates'], linestyle='-', marker='o', label="Annual graduates")

def millions(x, pos):
    'The two args are the value and tick position'
    return '%1.1fM' % (x*1e-6)

formatter = FuncFormatter(millions)

#fig, ax = plt.subplots()
ax.yaxis.set_major_formatter(formatter)

ax.legend(loc=2)
ax.set_xlabel("Year");
ax.set_ylabel("Population");

dx = -0.3
dy = -6*(10**6)

            xy=(df['year'][0]+dx, df['population'][0]+dy+(-3*(10**6))))
